Responses\:
    success
    failure
93556cac-5653-4293-98cf-6c5ef1664e10.17daf825-ca5a-47f0-a0d0-431b34fec967.prompt=Database Name\: 93556cac-5653-4293-98cf-6c5ef1664e10.315b3ff0-b91f-4549-9533-dd947be51eeb.prompt=HostName\: 93556cac-5653-4293-98cf-6c5ef1664e10.51f6fc47-a99b-4c5f-b0e4-6a76dac0b963.description=This operation runs a SQL command. Inputs\: DBServerName - The hostname or ip address of the database server. DbType - The type of database to connect to. Valid values\: Oracle, MSSQL, Sybase, Netcool, DB2 and Custom. Default value\: Oracle Username - The username to use when connecting to the database. Password - The password to use when connecting to the database. instance - The name instance (for MSSQL Server). Leave it blank for default instance. DbPort - The port to connect to. Default values\: Oracle\: 1521, MSSQL\: 1433, Sybase\: 5000, Netcool\: 4100, DB2\: 50000. Database - The name of the database. authenticationType - The type of authentication used to access the database (applicable only to MSSQL type). Valid values\: sql, windows (for MSSQL) Default value\: sql dbClass - The classname of the JDBC driver to use. dbURL - The url required to load up the driver and make your connection. Command - The command to execute. timeout - Seconds to wait before timing out the SQL command execution. When the default value is used, there is no limit on the amount of time allowed for a running command to complete. Default value\: 0 databasePoolingProperties - Properties for database pooling configuration. This parameter replaces the databasePooling.properties file from 9x version (you may copy-paste the file content here). Pooling is disabled by default. For more details check the /Library/Operations/Database/JDBC folder description. Example\: db.pooling.enable\=true resultSetType - the result set type. See JDBC folder description for more details. Valid values\: TYPE_FORWARD_ONLY, TYPE_SCROLL_INSENSITIVE,TYPE_SCROLL_SENSITIVE. Default value\: TYPE_FORWARD_ONLY resultSetConcurrency - the result set concurrency. See JDBC folder description for more details. Valid values\: CONCUR_READ_ONLY, CONCUR_UPDATABLE Default value\: CONCUR_READ_ONLY Results\: returnResult - This is the primary output. It contains the "Command completed successfully" message if the operation succeeded, or a failure message otherwise. outputText - The return result of SQL command. updateCount - The update count of the command executed. Responses\: success - The command was executed successfully. failure - Failed to execute the command. Note\: 1. Check the JDBC folder description for details on how to load database connectors. 2. In case of using subprograms like (GET_LINE, GET_LINES, NEW_LINE, PUT, PUT_LUNE) from DBMS_OUTPUT package, the DBMS_OUTPUT.ENABLE() declaration should be used before of these calls. 93556cac-5653-4293-98cf-6c5ef1664e10.69799e67-1f23-46be-a0eb-ee0508aa2861.prompt=HostName\: 93556cac-5653-4293-98cf-6c5ef1664e10.8a46a938-2865-41db-bca6-32b05f9e5b1f.description=

93556cac-5653-4293-98cf-6c5ef1664e10.aa10e021-ff86-4b67-9cea-e2c770a19ae8.description=
This operation reads all contents of a file into the Result variable.

Input Parameters\:
filename 	- The name of the file to read.
characterSet - Character set encoding of the file. Defaults to UTF-8.

Result\:
Contents of the file.

Responses\:
success	 - Successfully read the file.
failure	 - Could not read the file.
